{"title_page": "Sho Otsuka", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name=Sho Otsuka<br/>\u5927\u585a \u7fd4\n|image=\n|image_size=\n|caption=\n|fullname=Sho Otsuka\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1995|7|25}}\n|birth_place=[[Toyama Prefecture|Toyama]], [[Japan]]\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n|height={{Height|m=1.71}}\n|position=[[Midfielder]]\n|currentclub=[[FC Ryukyu]]\n|clubnumber=24\n|youthyears1=2014\u20132017|youthclubs1=[[Kwansei Gakuin University]]\n|years1=2018\u2013|clubs1=[[FC Ryukyu]]|caps1=1|goals1=0\n|totalcaps=1|totalgoals=0\n|nationalyears1=|nationalteam1=|nationalcaps1=|nationalgoals1=\n|manageryears1=|managerclubs1=\n|medaltemplates=\n|club-update=5 January 2019\n|nationalteam-update=\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Sho Otsuka'''|\u5927\u585a \u7fd4|Otsuka Sho|born July 25, 1995}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[Association football|football]] player.<ref>{{J.League player}}</ref>\n\n==Playing career==\nOtsuka was born in [[Toyama Prefecture]] on July 25, 1995. After graduating from [[Kwansei Gakuin University]], he joined [[J3 League]] club [[FC Ryukyu]] in 2018.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{J.League player}}\n\n{{FC Ryukyu squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Otsuka, Sho}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Kwansei Gakuin University alumni]]\n[[Category:Association football people from Toyama Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:J3 League players]]\n[[Category:FC Ryukyu players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n\n\n{{Japan-footy-midfielder-1990s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name=Sho Otsuka<br/>\u5927\u585a \u7fd4\n|image=\n|image_size=\n|caption=\n|fullname=Sho Otsuka\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1995|7|25}}\n|birth_place=[[Toyama Prefecture|Toyama]], [[Japan]]\n|death_date=\n|death_place=\n|height={{Height|m=1.71}}\n|position=[[Midfielder]]\n|currentclub=[[FC Ryukyu]]\n|clubnumber=24\n|youthyears1=2014\u20132017|youthclubs1=[[Kwansei Gakuin University]]\n|years1=2018\u2013|clubs1=[[FC Ryukyu]]|caps1=1|goals1=0\n|totalcaps=1|totalgoals=0\n|nationalyears1=|nationalteam1=|nationalcaps1=|nationalgoals1=\n|manageryears1=|managerclubs1=\n|medaltemplates=\n|club-update=5 January 2019\n|nationalteam-update=\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Sho Otsuka'''|\u5927\u585a \u7fd4|Otsuka Sho|born July 25, 1995}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[Association football|football]] player.<ref>{{J.League player}}</ref>\n\n==Playing career==\nOtsuka was born in [[Toyama Prefecture]] on July 25, 1995. After graduating from [[Kwansei Gakuin University]], he joined [[J3 League]] club [[FC Ryukyu]] in 2018.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{J.League player}}\n\n{{FC Ryukyu squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Otsuka, Sho}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Kwansei Gakuin University alumni]]\n[[Category:Association football people from Toyama Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:J3 League players]]\n[[Category:FC Ryukyu players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n\n\n{{Japan-footy-midfielder-1990s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"Japanese footballer\", overriding Wikidata description \"Japanese association football player\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sho_Otsuka"}
