{"title_page": "New Zealand cricket team in the West Indies in 1995\u201396", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n\nThe [[New Zealand national cricket team]] toured the [[West Indies]] from March to May 1996 and played a two-match [[Test cricket|Test series]] against the [[West Indies cricket team]] which the West Indies won 1\u20130. New Zealand were captained by [[Lee Germon]]; the West Indies by [[Courtney Walsh]]. In addition, the teams played a five-match [[Limited Overs International]] (LOI) series which the West Indies won 3\u20132.<ref name=\"CATI\">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Events/2/New_Zealand_in_West_Indies_and_Bermuda_1995-96.html |publisher=CricketArchive |title=New Zealand in the West Indies 1996 |accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n==One Day Internationals (ODIs)==\n\nThe West Indies won the series 3-2.\n\n===1st ODI===\n{{Limited overs matches\n| date = 26 March 1996\n| time = \n| daynight = \n| team1 = {{cr-rt|NZL}}\n| team2 = {{cr|WIN}}\n\n| score1 = 243 (49.1 overs)\n| runs1 = [[Dipak Patel (cricketer)|DN Patel]] 71 (58)\n| wickets1 = [[Curtly Ambrose|CEL Ambrose]] 4/36 (10 overs)\n\n| score2 = 247/9 (49.1 overs)\n| runs2 = [[Stuart Williams (cricketer)|SC Williams]] 62 (90)\n| wickets2 = [[Chris Harris (cricketer)|CZ Harris]] 3/45 (10 overs)\n\n| result = West Indies won by 1 wicket\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/61/61972.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Sabina Park]], [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]], [[Jamaica]]\n| umpires = [[Lloyd Barker|LH Barker]] and [[Steve Bucknor|SA Bucknor]]\n| motm = [[Dipak Patel (cricketer)|DN Patel]] (NZ)\n| toss = West Indies won the toss and elected to field.\n| rain = \n| notes = [[Ridley Jacobs|RD Jacobs]] (WI) made his ODI debut.\n}}\n\n===2nd ODI===\n{{Limited overs matches\n| date = 29 March 1996\n| time = \n| daynight = \n| team1 = {{cr-rt|WIN}}\n| team2 = {{cr|NZL}}\n\n| score1 = 238/7 (50 overs)\n| runs1 = [[Roland Holder|RIC Holder]] 65 (48)\n| wickets1 = [[Nathan Astle|NJ Astle]] 2/32 (9 overs)\n\n| score2 = 239/6 (49.5 overs)\n| runs2 = [[Stephen Fleming|SP Fleming]] 106[[not out|*]] (108)\n| wickets2 = [[Curtly Ambrose|CEL Ambrose]] 2/42 (9.5 overs)\n\n| result = New Zealand won by 4 wickets\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/61/61980.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Queen's Park Oval]], [[Port of Spain]], [[Trinidad]]\n| umpires = [[Lloyd Barker|LH Barker]] and [[Steve Bucknor|SA Bucknor]]\n| motm = [[Stephen Fleming|SP Fleming]] (NZ)\n| toss = New Zealand won the toss and elected to field.\n| rain = \n| notes = \n}}\n\n===3rd ODI===\n{{Limited overs matches\n| date = 30 March 1996\n| time = \n| daynight = \n| team1 = {{cr-rt|NZL}}\n| team2 = {{cr|WIN}}\n\n| score1 = 219/8 (50 overs)\n| runs1 = [[Roger Twose|RG Twose]] 48 (70)\n| wickets1 = [[Roger Harper|RA Harper]] 2/45 (10 overs)\n\n| score2 = 225/3 (45.4 overs)\n| runs2 = [[Brian Lara|BC Lara]] 146[[not out|*]] (134)\n| wickets2 = [[Gavin Larsen|GR Larsen]] 3/26 (8.4 overs)\n\n| result = West Indies won by 7 wickets\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/61/61982.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Queen's Park Oval]], [[Port of Spain]], [[Trinidad]]\n| umpires = [[Lloyd Barker|LH Barker]] and [[Steve Bucknor|SA Bucknor]]\n| motm = [[Brian Lara|BC Lara]] (WI)\n| toss = New Zealand won the toss and elected to bat.\n| rain = \n| notes = [[Laurie Williams (cricketer)|LR Williams]] (WI) made his ODI debut.\n}}\n\n===4th ODI===\n{{Limited overs matches\n| date = 3 April 1996\n| time = \n| daynight = \n| team1 = {{cr-rt|NZL}}\n| team2 = {{cr|WIN}}\n\n| score1 = 158 (35.5 overs)\n| runs1 = [[Craig Spearman|CM Spearman]] 41 (39)\n| wickets1 = [[Laurie Williams (cricketer)|LR Williams]] 3/16 (4.5 overs)\n\n| score2 = 154 (49.1 overs)\n| runs2 = [[Roland Holder|RIC Holder]] 49[[not out|*]] (86)\n| wickets2 = [[Chris Cairns|CL Cairns]] 2/17 (5.1 overs)\n\n| result = New Zealand won by 4 runs\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/61/61989.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Bourda]], [[Georgetown, Guyana|Georgetown]], [[Guyana]]\n| umpires = [[Clyde Duncan (umpire)|CR Duncan]] and [[Eddie Nicholls|EA Nicholls]]\n| motm = [[New Zealand national cricket team|New Zealand team]]\n| toss = West Indies won the toss and elected to field.\n| rain = \n| notes = \n}}\n\n===5th ODI===\n{{Limited overs matches\n| date = 6 April 1996\n| time = \n| daynight = \n| team1 = {{cr-rt|NZL}}\n| team2 = {{cr|WIN}}\n\n| score1 = 241/8 (50 overs)\n| runs1 = [[Stephen Fleming|SP Fleming]] 75 (102)\n| wickets1 = [[Jimmy Adams|JC Adams]] 3/50 (10 overs)\n\n| score2 = 242/3 (48.3 overs)\n| runs2 = [[Brian Lara|BC Lara]] 104 (103)\n| wickets2 = [[Dipak Patel (cricketer)|DN Patel]] 1/46 (10 overs)\n\n| result = West Indies won by 7 wickets\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/61/61993.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Arnos Vale Stadium]], [[Kingstown]], [[St. Vincent and the Grenadines]]\n| umpires = [[Lloyd Barker|LH Barker]] and [[Basil Morgan|BEW Morgan]]\n| motm = [[Phil Simmons|PV Simmons]] (WI)\n| toss = West Indies won the toss and elected to field.\n| rain = \n| notes = \n}}\n\n==Test series summary==\n\n===First Test===\n{{Two-innings cricket match\n| date = 19\u201323 April 1996<br>(5\u2013day match)\n| team1 = {{cr-rt|NZL}}\n| team2 = {{cr|WIN}}\n\n| score-team1-inns1 = 195 (62 overs)\n| runs-team1-inns1 = [[Adam Parore|AC Parore]] 59 (112)\n| wickets-team1-inns1 = [[Jimmy Adams|JC Adams]] 5/17 (9 overs)\n\n| score-team2-inns1 = 472 (164.3 overs)\n| runs-team2-inns1 = [[Sherwin Campbell|SL Campbell]] 208 (470)\n| wickets-team2-inns1 = [[Gavin Larsen|GR Larsen]] 3/76 (40 overs)\n\n| score-team1-inns2 = 305 (82 overs)\n| runs-team1-inns2 = [[Nathan Astle|NJ Astle]] 125 (150)\n| wickets-team1-inns2 = [[Ian Bishop (cricketer)|IR Bishop]] 4/67 (19 overs)\n\n| score-team2-inns2 = 29/0 (4 overs)\n| runs-team2-inns2 = [[Sherwin Campbell|SL Campbell]] 29[[not out|*]] (21)\n| wickets-team2-inns2 =\n\n| result = West Indies won by 10 wickets\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/62/62019.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Kensington Oval]], [[Bridgetown]], [[Barbados]]\n| umpires = [[Steve Bucknor|SA Bucknor]] (WI) and [[Peter Willey|P Willey]] (ENG)\n| motm = [[Sherwin Campbell|SL Campbell]] (WI)\n| toss = West Indies won the toss and elected to field.\n| rain = 22 April was taken as a rest day.''\n*''The match was scheduled for five days but completed in four.\n| notes = [[Robert Samuels|RG Samuels]] and [[Patterson Thompson|PIC Thompson]] (both WI) made their Test debuts.\n}}\n\n===Second Test===\n{{Two-innings cricket match\n| date = 27 April\u20132 May 1996<br>(5\u2013day match)\n| team1 = {{cr-rt|WIN}}\n| team2 = {{cr|NZL}}\n\n| score-team1-inns1 = 548/7[[Declaration and forfeiture|d]] (166 overs)\n| runs-team1-inns1 = [[Jimmy Adams|JC Adams]] 208[[not out|*]] (333)\n| wickets-team1-inns1 = [[Chris Harris (cricketer)|CZ Harris]] 2/83 (35 overs)\n\n| score-team2-inns1 = 437 (144.3 overs)\n| runs-team2-inns1 = [[Nathan Astle|NJ Astle]] 103 (165)\n| wickets-team2-inns1 = [[Curtly Ambrose|CEL Ambrose]] 5/68 (32 overs)\n\n| score-team1-inns2 = 184 (61.3 overs)\n| runs-team1-inns2 = [[Brian Lara|BC Lara]] 74 (119)\n| wickets-team1-inns2 = [[Danny Morrison (cricketer)|DK Morrison]] 5/61 (20 overs)\n\n| score-team2-inns2 = 130/5 (65 overs)\n| runs-team2-inns2 = [[Stephen Fleming|SP Fleming]] 56 (172)\n| wickets-team2-inns2 = [[Curtly Ambrose|CEL Ambrose]] 2/22 (12 overs)\n\n| result = Match drawn\n| report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/62/62045.html Scorecard]\n| venue = [[Antigua Recreation Ground]], [[St. John's, Antigua and Barbuda|St. John's]], [[Antigua]]\n| umpires = [[Lloyd Barker|LH Barker]] (WI) and [[Cyril Mitchley|CJ Mitchley]] (SA)\n| motm = [[Jimmy Adams|JC Adams]] (WI)\n| toss = New Zealand won the toss and elected to field.\n| rain = 30 April was taken as a rest day.\n| notes = This Test set a record for the highest match aggregate (1299 runs) without a [[Bye (cricket)|bye]] being scored.<ref name=\"Walmsley\">{{cite book|last1=Walmsley|first1=Keith|title=Mosts Without in Test Cricket|date=2003|publisher=Keith Walmsley|location=Reading, England|isbn=0947540067|pages=375}}</ref>\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*\n\n{{International cricket tours of the West Indies}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:New Zealand cricket team in the West Indies in 1995-96}}\n[[Category:1996 in New Zealand cricket]]\n[[Category:1996 in West Indian cricket]]\n[[Category:New Zealand cricket tours of the West Indies|1995-96]]\n[[Category:International cricket competitions from 1994\u201395 to 1997]]\n[[Category:West Indian cricket seasons from 1970\u201371 to 1999\u20132000]]\n\n\n{{WestIndies-cricket-tour-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n\nThe [[New Zealand national cricket team]] toured the [[West Indies]] from March to May 1996 and played a two-match [[Test cricket|Test series]] against the [[West Indies cricket team]] which the West Indies won 1\u20130. New Zealand were captained by [[Lee Germon]]; the West Indies by [[Courtney Walsh]]. In addition, the teams played a five-match [[Limited Overs International]] (LOI) series which the West Indies won 3\u20132.<ref name=\"CATI\">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Events/2/New_Zealand_in_West_Indies_and_Bermuda_1995-96.html |publisher=CricketArchive |title=New Zealand in the West Indies 1996 |accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n==One Day Internationals (ODIs)==\n\nThe West Indies won the series 3-2.\n\n===1st ODI===\n{{Limited overs matches\n| date = 26 March 1996\n| time = \n| daynight = \n| team1 = {{cr-rt|NZL}}\n| team2 = {{cr|WIN}}\n\n| score1 = 243 (49.1 overs)\n| runs1 = [[Dipak Patel (cricketer)|DN Patel]] 71 (58)\n| wickets1 = [[Curtly Ambrose|CEL Ambrose]] 4/36 (10 overs)\n\n| score2 = 247/9 (49.1 overs)\n