{"title_page": "Little Birds (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Little Birds\n| image                    = \n| alt                      = \n| genre                    = [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n| runtime                  = 60 minutes\n| company                  = Warp Films\n| distributor              = \n| creator                  = \n| producer                 = \n| executive_producer       = Ruth McCance<br>Peter Carlton\n| cinematography           = \n| starring                 = \n| language                 = English\n| network                  = [[Sky Atlantic]]\n| picture_format           = [[16:9]] [[1080p]]\n| audio_format             = [[Stereophonic sound|Stereo]]\n| first_aired              = \n| last_aired               = \n| num_series               = 1\n| num_episodes             = \n| list_episodes            = \n}}\n'''''Little Birds'''''  is an upcoming [[Sky Atlantic]] original drama [[television series]] starring [[Juno Temple]] and produced by Warp Films.\n\nPlayfully inspired by [[Ana\u00efs Nin]]\u2019s infamous collection of erotic short stories, ''Little Birds'' weaves stories of love and desire together with personal drama and political intrigue, set against a uniquely distinctive backdrop of hedonism and conflict. Little Birds is filmed on location in Andalucia with studio elements in Manchester.\n\n==Premise==\n''Little Birds'' is set in Tangier in 1955, in the famous \u2018international zone\u2019 - one of the last outposts of colonial decadence, and a culture shock in more ways than one for troubled American debutante Lucy Savage (Juno Temple). Lucy desires an unconventional life free from the societal cage she\u2019s been kept in and, along with Tangier itself, finds herself on the cusp of achieving a painful yet necessary independence. \n\n==Cast==\n*[[Juno Temple]] as Lucy Savage\n*[[Yumna Marwan]] as Cherifa Lamour\n*David Costabile as Grant Savage\n*[[Raphael Acloque]] as Adham Abaza\n*[[Hugh Skinner]] as Hugo Cavendish-Smyth\n*[[Jean-Marc Barr]] as Secretary Pierre Vaney\n*[[Rossy De Palma]] as Contessa Mandrax\n*[[Nina Sosanya]] as Lili von X\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links==\n*{{IMDb title|id=9849190|title=Little Birds}}\n\n{{Sky Atlantic}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Little Birds (TV Series)}}\n[[Category:2020 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2020s British drama television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Sky Atlantic television programmes]]\n[[Category:Television series set in 1955]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Little Birds\n| image                    = \n| alt                      = \n| genre                    = [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n| runtime                  = 60 minutes\n| company                  = Warp Films\n| distributor              = \n| creator                  = \n| producer                 = \n| executive_producer       = Ruth McCance<br>Peter Carlton\n| cinematography           = \n| starring                 = \n| language                 = English\n| network                  = [[Sky Atlantic]]\n| picture_format           = [[16:9]] [[1080p]]\n| audio_format             = [[Stereophonic sound|Stereo]]\n| first_aired              = \n| last_aired               = \n| num_series               = 1\n| num_episodes             = \n| list_episodes            = \n}}\n'''''Little Birds'''''  is an upcoming [[Sky Atlantic]] original drama [[television series]] starring [[Juno Temple]] and produced by Warp Films.\n\n\nPlayfully inspired by [[Ana\u00efs Nin]]\u2019s infamous collection of erotic short stories, ''Little Birds'' weaves stories of love and desire together with personal drama and political intrigue, set against a uniquely distinctive backdrop of hedonism and conflict. Little Birds is filmed on location in Andalucia with studio elements in Manchester.\n\n==Premise==\n''Little Birds'' is set in Tangier in 1955, in the famous \u2018international zone\u2019 - one of the last outposts of colonial decadence, and a culture shock in more ways than one for troubled American debutante Lucy Savage (Juno Temple). Lucy desires an unconventional life free from the societal cage she\u2019s been kept in and, along with Tangier itself, finds herself on the cusp of achieving a painful yet necessary independence. \n\n==Cast==\n*[[Juno Temple]] as Lucy Savage\n*[[Yumna Marwan]] as Cherifa Lamour\n*David Costabile as Grant Savage\n*[[Raphael Acloque]] as Adham Abaza\n*[[Hugh Skinner]] as Hugo Cavendish-Smyth\n*[[Jean-Marc Barr]] as Secretary Pierre Vaney\n*[[Rossy De Palma]] as Contessa Mandrax\n*[[Nina Sosanya]] as Lili von X\n\n== References ==\n== External links==\n*{{IMDb title|id=9849190|title=Little Birds}}\n\n{{Sky Atlantic}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Little Birds (TV Series)}}\n[[Category:2020 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2020s British drama television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Sky Atlantic television programmes]]\n[[Category:Television series set in 1955]]\n", "name_user": "6ii9", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Little_Birds_(TV_series)"}
